steps.instruction:
For a more step by step guide, look [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2016/08/08/pane-bianco-bakealong)

### Making The Dough
- Combine 3 cups of flour, 2 teaspoons of instant yeast, one large egg, 1/2 cup of lukewarm milk, 1/3 cup of lukewarm water and 3 tablespoons of olive oil
- Mix and knead till the dough is smooth and very soft. The dough should stick to the bottom of the bowl if using a stand mixer
- Place the dough into a lightly greased bowl for 45 to 60 minutes to rise

### Making The Filling
- Drain the oil from the sun dried tomatoes, patting them dry
- Chop / cut the tomatoes into smaller bits
- Mince the garlic
- Chop the basil

### Shaping The Dough
- When the dough is finished rising, gently deflate the dough and flatten it into a 22x8.5 inch rectangle
- Spread the cheese, tomatoes, garlic and basil
- Starting with one long edge, roll the dough into a log the long way
- Pinch the edges to seal
- Place the log seam-side down on a lightly greased or parchment paper lined backing sheet
- Using kitchen shears, start 1/2 inch from one end and cut the log lengthwise down the center about 1 inch deep till you reach 1/2 inch from the other end
- Keeping the cut side up, form an "S" shape
- Tuck both ends under the center of the "S"
- Pinch both ends to seal
- Cover and let rise in a warm place for 45 to 60 minutes

### Baking
- Preheat the oven to 350F
- Bake for 20 to 25 minutes
- Cover with tinfoil
- Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes
- Let cool to room temperature before serving
